1. Report Status Summary ✅

Published Reports Count – display the total number of published reports, maybe with a green checkmark or badge.

Draft Reports Count – total drafts, with a yellow or orange warning icon.

Not Published / Pending Reports – optional, with a grey or neutral icon.

2. Submission Activity 📊

Organizations Submitted – number of orgs that submitted their report, building icon.

Organizations Pending / Not Submitted – number of orgs yet to submit, warning icon.

Latest Submission Time – last report submitted, clock icon.

Submission Trend – small bar or line chart showing submissions: Today / This week / This month.

Top Submitting Organizations – maybe top 3 orgs with fastest submission, trophy or medal icon.

3. Recent Activity Feed 📋

“Report X was published” – green check icon, shows which report went live.

“Organization Y submitted report Z” – building icon, time-stamped.

“Draft X was updated” – pencil icon.

“Report Z marked Not Approved” – red cross icon, with reason tooltip.

Time Ago Display – e.g., “5 mins ago”, “2 hours ago”, so admin can quickly see recency.